track_notes: I hiked up the Crooked Arm Trail to the Indian Grave Gap trail.  I went past the summit until the trail crested the ridge.  I immediately started a steep 100 yrd+ bushwhack up the right hand ridge to within the AZ following a faint path. Track is my return path of 3.73 miles.  I would recommend going via the Rich Mtn Trail starting at Rich Mtn Gap as it would be shorter and less elevation gain.  See https://www.nps.gov/grsm/planyourvisit/upload/GSMNP-Map_JUNE14-complete4-2.pdf

Beginning at the Rich Mtn TH at Ace Gap, we climbed turning left at the Indian Grave Gap Trail continuing to 35.62675, -83.77812 where we began a short but steep bushwhack to the summit. Return was the reverse course. 6.5 mi RT with 1,800 ft EG.  Backcountry campsite #5 is very close to the Rich Mtn/Indian Grave Gap Trail and would make a great overnight for this summit after doing Rich Mtn.  Dean ~ K2JB
track_title: W4T/SU-046, Scott Mtn From Rich Mtn Trailhead

track_notes: Thanks K2JB for the initial beta, and I followed the Crooked Arm Ridge trail up from the Cades Cove parking area.  The trail past the junction for camp 6 does get into a bit of a Rhododendron Tunnel; however about 1/2 mile before the other routes turn off to reach the AZ, there is a clearing of Rhododendron about 50-60 yards wide that can be switchbacked up off trail.  It is steep, and its hard going for about 100 yards, but once you achieve the ridge line its a straight walk with out a lot of ground cover to bushwhack.  NOTE:  There are a few big widowmakers on the summit and do be aware that the summit is also the border between public and private lands.
track_title: Crazy uphill offtrail to achieve the summit proper
